  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Nepal ECD Programme</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The ECD programme is a bilateral programme which NRCS has been implementing in partnership with British Red Cross from February to Decemen 2019. The programme covers three wards (3 4 and 5) of Mahankal Rural Municiaplity Lalitpur district. The programme covers 3 major areas; Outcome 1: Livelihoods - Vulnerable communities have strengthened and improved food security and income through increased access to livelihood strategies improved market linkages and financial services. Outcome 2: Health and WASH- Hygiene and well-being is improved through increased access to water sanitation and health education. Outcome 3: NRCS capacity building- NRCS and its district and sub-chapter have increased programme management capacity.</narrative>
  </description>
